- Collection is an Object that holds references to other objects. aka Data Structure
- Collections framework consist of Interfaces Classes and Methods to store and manipulate data.
- Collection Framework: Collection is an Interface

Set - Unordered unique elements   Set<Integer> mySet = new HashSet();
List - Ordered elements which can be accessed by their position     ArrayList <String> myList = new ArrayList<>();
Queue - Ordered element for processing. Access in the order element were added. (FIFO - fist in first out)

Map is not a true collection (does not inherit from Collection Interface)
Map - Unordered unique key-value pair    Map <String, Integer> myMap = new HashMap<>();